The article is a speech given by the First Lady of the United States, Jill Biden, in Mexico City. She expresses gratitude to Patty, who has represented the United States and strengthened communities in Mexico. She also thanks Ambassador Salazar, Hope, and Andrea for hosting the event. The speech focuses on the power of Mexican-American art and the importance of uplifting women's stories to inspire others. Biden acknowledges the struggles women face in raising their voices and fighting for a seat at the table. She emphasizes that when women are given opportunities, they can achieve great things and contribute to economic growth and societal stability. Biden mentions the release of the U.S. Strategy on Global Women's Economic Security by the Biden-Harris Administration, which aims to promote gender parity and support women entrepreneurs globally. She expresses admiration for the women entrepreneurs in Mexico and their courage in starting businesses and mentoring the next generation of women leaders.